In [Performance Strategies For Low-Bandwith Connections|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DISC/Performance+Strategies+For+Low-Bandwith+Connections] we say:
{quote}
h4. Avoid The Rich Text Editor

The wiki markup editor loads significantly faster than the rich text editor, so it may be worthwhile teaching users how to use wikimarkup and then setting it as default. Another option is to edit via an offline client such as Microsoft Word using the Office Connector plugin, though upload may still be slow and this doesn't cover commenting.
{quote}

Wiki markup is no longer available in most of supported releases. We should delete that paragraph or advice that it is only valid for versions prior Confluence 4.x.

