*This bug was introduced in 5.0-rc1. It was working well in 5.0-beta4*

So here's the deal.

We have a servlet we render in our own iframe and we use the {{ResourceManager}} to manage all our resources dependencies.

In the page we render we do the following:
{code}
<html>
<head>
    $webResourceManager.requireResource("com.comalatech.workflow:awpremote")
    $webResourceManager.includeResources($resp.getWriter(),$urlMode,$resourceFilter)

</head>
<body>
</body>
</html>
{code}

We render only our own resources so we provide our own {{$resourceFilter}}:
{code}
public class ComalatechWebResourceFilter extends DefaultWebResourceFilter {
    @Override
    public boolean matches(String resourceName) {
        return resourceName.contains("com.comalatech.workflow") && super.matches(resourceName);
    }
}
{code}

This worked well up until *5.0-beta4*, as each resource has its plugin module key prefixed in the {{resourceName}}:
{code}
...
com.atlassian.plugins.shortcuts.atlassian-shortcuts-plugin:shortcuts.js
com.atlassian.confluence.keyboardshortcuts:confluence-keyboard-shortcuts.js
com.atlassian.auiplugin:aui-experimental-dropdown2.js
com.comalatech.workflow:aui5dependencies.js
...
{code}

However, *in 5.0-rc1* the key is not longer there!
{code}
...
shortcuts.js
confluence-keyboard-shortcuts.js
aui-experimental-dropdown2.js
aui5dependencies.js
...
{code}

The reason why we do this is that WebResource manager includes tons of atlassian stuff, even it it was not requested through {{webResourceManager.requireResource}} :-(

