The inline dialog being triggered is being forced to always go down, and scale according to the available space. Right now this isn't a big issue, but lets do it right…

Attached to the issue, is a pic of the issue, and in my mind the quicker solution is to say the inline dialog should display at least 11 child nodes, and if there isn't enough space then shift it up.

Other issues that have been noticed is that scrolling on the page dismisses the inline dialog. As per the ADG spec the inline dialog should be removed only on a click outside or by clicking a second time on the triggering element. (I don't think we are using a timeout to dismiss right now, but if we are lets not do that…)
